JOHANNESBURG - Acting SARS Commissioner Mark Kingon says the country has a tough tax season ahead of it. The revenue collector needs over R1.3-trillion to reach their target. The last season saw a shortfall of around R50-billion, mostly because of weak growth, administrative challenges and tax avoidance. READ: SARS cuts short tax filing period Kingon also said the service's credibility will be restored. It's been dogged by numerous scandals in recent years. eNCA